<template><div><p>Implementing <mark>internationalization</mark> in the theme only requires some simple configurations.</p>
<p>Let's take an example of creating a project with <strong>Chinese</strong> as the default language and including <strong>English</strong> and <strong>French</strong>.</p>
<h2 id="directory-structure" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#directory-structure"><span>Directory Structure</span></a></h2>
<p>First, you need to create a directory structure similar to the following:</p>
<div class="vp-file-tree"><ul>
<FileTreeItem type="folder" :expanded="true" :empty="false"><span class="tree-node folder"><VPIcon name="vscode-icons:folder-type-docs"></VPIcon><span class="name">docs</span></span>
<ul>
<FileTreeItem type="folder" :expanded="true" :empty="false"><span class="tree-node folder"><VPIcon name="vscode-icons:default-folder"></VPIcon><span class="name focus"><strong>en</strong></span><span class="comment">  # English directory</span></span>
<ul>
<FileTreeItem type="file" :expanded="false" :empty="true"><span class="tree-node file"><VPIcon name="vscode-icons:file-type-markdown"></VPIcon><span class="name">foo.md</span></span></FileTreeItem>
<FileTreeItem type="file" :expanded="false" :empty="true"><span class="tree-node file"><VPIcon name="flat-color-icons:info"></VPIcon><span class="name">README.md</span><span class="comment"> # English home page</span></span></FileTreeItem>
</ul>
</FileTreeItem>
<FileTreeItem type="folder" :expanded="true" :empty="false"><span class="tree-node folder"><VPIcon name="vscode-icons:default-folder"></VPIcon><span class="name focus"><strong>fr</strong></span><span class="comment">  # French directory</span></span>
<ul>
<FileTreeItem type="file" :expanded="false" :empty="true"><span class="tree-node file"><VPIcon name="vscode-icons:file-type-markdown"></VPIcon><span class="name">foo.md</span></span></FileTreeItem>
<FileTreeItem type="file" :expanded="false" :empty="true"><span class="tree-node file"><VPIcon name="flat-color-icons:info"></VPIcon><span class="name">README.md</span><span class="comment"> # French home page</span></span></FileTreeItem>
</ul>
</FileTreeItem>
<FileTreeItem type="file" :expanded="false" :empty="true"><span class="tree-node file"><VPIcon name="vscode-icons:file-type-markdown"></VPIcon><span class="name">foo.md</span></span></FileTreeItem>
<FileTreeItem type="file" :expanded="false" :empty="true"><span class="tree-node file"><VPIcon name="flat-color-icons:info"></VPIcon><span class="name">README.md</span><span class="comment"> # Chinese home page</span></span></FileTreeItem>
</ul>
</FileTreeItem>
</ul>
</div><p>Here, <code v-pre>docs/en/</code> is used to store <strong>English</strong> documents, <code v-pre>docs/fr/</code> stores <strong>French</strong> documents, and <strong>Chinese</strong> documents are stored directly under <code v-pre>docs/</code>.</p>
<div class="hint-container important">
<p class="hint-container-title">Consistent directory and file names across languages</p>
<p>Try to keep the file names and directory names consistent across different language directories. This helps the theme correctly navigate to different language versions of the article when switching languages.</p>
</div>
<h2 id="vuepress-configuration" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#vuepress-configuration"><span>VuePress Configuration</span></a></h2>
<h3 id="default-language" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#default-language"><span>Default Language</span></a></h3>
<p>In <code v-pre>.vuepress/config.ts</code>, declare the default language:</p>
