<div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true" style="counter-reset:line-number 0"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div></template></CodeTabs><h3 id="adding-other-languages" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#adding-other-languages"><span>Adding Other Languages</span></a></h3>
<p>You need to set the <code v-pre>lang</code> option for each language. Even if you are only using a single language, you must set <code v-pre>lang</code> in <code v-pre>.vuepress/config.{js,ts}</code>.</p>
<div class="hint-container tip">
<p class="hint-container-title">Why do this?</p>
<p>To provide the correct locale text, the theme needs to know which language is being used in the root folder and each multilingual folder.</p>
</div>
<p>Configure in <code v-pre>.vuepress/config.ts</code>:</p>
